trans-unit.source: Represents an unsigned rights managed <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"></xref> or an unsigned <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"></xref> template.
trans-unit.target: Rappresenta un unsigned rights Management <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"> </xref> o unsigned <xref href="System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense"> </xref> modello.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> defines security data about rights, users, and other security-related information.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>Definisce i dati di sicurezza relativi diritti, utenti e altre informazioni relative alla sicurezza.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: The license defines how a specific user on a specific computer can use specified rights-managed content.
trans-unit.target: La licenza definisce come un utente specifico in un computer specifico può utilizzare contenuto protetto da rights Management specificato.

trans-unit.source: The publishing process begins with the document author, who defines rights information in an UnsignedPublishLicense.
trans-unit.target: Il processo di pubblicazione inizia con l'autore del documento, che definisce le informazioni sui diritti in un UnsignedPublishLicense.

trans-unit.source: Next, the authoring application calls the UnsignedPublishLicense.<xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A> method to create a signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>.
trans-unit.target: Successivamente, l'applicazione di creazione e modifica chiama il UnsignedPublishLicense. <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A>metodo per creare un <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> con segno</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UnsignedPublishLicense.Sign%2A>

trans-unit.source: The signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> can then be provided to the end-user client application which can call <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A> to request an end-user <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>.
trans-unit.target: Firmato <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>può quindi essere fornito all'applicazione client per l'utente finale che è possibile chiamare <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A>per richiedere agli utenti finali <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense.AcquireUseLicense%2A> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: The returned <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense> then allows the client application to exercise the rights that are granted to the user.
trans-unit.target: L'oggetto restituito <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>quindi consente all'applicazione client di esercitare i diritti vengono concessi all'utente.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.UseLicense>

trans-unit.source: The document author can use the UnsignedPublishLicense class either to create a signed <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>, or to build and serialize a <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> template.
trans-unit.target: L'autore del documento possa utilizzare la classe di UnsignedPublishLicense sia per creare un oggetto firmato <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>, o per compilare e serializzare un <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>modello.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense> </xref:System.Security.RightsManagement.PublishLicense>

trans-unit.source: As with other <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement> types, UnsignedPublishLicense is only usable in full trust applications.
trans-unit.target: Come con gli altri <xref:System.Security.RightsManagement>tipi, UnsignedPublishLicense è disponibile solo in applicazioni con attendibilità totale.</xref:System.Security.RightsManagement>
